3 months ago
this for my take on the problem: from pypdf import PdfWriter import os pdfs = [] for item in os.listdir(): if os.path.isfile(item) and item.endswith(".pdf"): pdfs.append(item) if len(pdfs) > 0: if len(pdfs) == 1: print(f"{len(pdfs)} Pdfs Ready to be merged:") for i, pdf in enumerate(pdfs, 1): print(f"{i}.", pdf) pdfs.sort() rename = input("There is only one pdf. Do you want to merge anyway or rename? Answer with \"yes\" to merge, \"no\" to exit or \"rename\" to rename: ").lower().strip() if rename == "yes": print("Confirmed.") elif rename == "no": print("Understood. Exiting.") exit() elif rename == "rename": newname = input(f"Renaming Confirmed. Please enter what you would like to rename the pdf \"{pdfs[0]}\" to: ").strip() if not newname.endswith(".pdf"): newname = newname + ".pdf" try: os.rename(pdfs[0], str(newname)) print("Pdf Renamed. Exiting.") exit() except Exception as e: print("Pdf couldn't be renamed. Reason:", e) exit() else: print("Unknown Parameter Given. Exiting.") exit() else: print("No Pdfs Found! Exiting.") exit() consent = input("Do you want to merge all the pdfs? Answer with yes/no: ").lower().strip() merger = PdfWriter() if consent == "yes": final_name = input("Confirmed. Merging Pdfs. What would you like to name the merged pdf? ").strip() print(f"Confirmed, Making merged pdf with name \"{final_name}\"") if not final_name.endswith(".pdf"): final_name = final_name + ".pdf" for pdf in pdfs: try: merger.append(pdf) except Exception as e: print(f"PDF \"{pdf}\" couldn't be added. Exiting.") print("Reason:", e) exit() merger.write(f"{str(final_name)}.pdf") merger.close() elif consent == "no": print("Merging aborted. Exiting.") exit() else: print("Unknown parameter given. Exiting.")

import PyPDF2 def merge_pdf(input_pdf_1, input_pdf_2, output_pdf): pdf_merge = PyPDF2.PdfMerger() try: with open(input_pdf_1, 'rb') as pdf_1: pdf_merge.append(pdf_1) with open(input_pdf_2, 'rb') as pdf_2: pdf_merge.append(pdf_2) with open(output_pdf, 'wb') as output: pdf_merge.write(output) except Exception as e: print(e) print("PDF merge successfully") merge_pdf('pdf1.pdf', 'pdf2.pdf', 'merge_pdf.pdf')

@SahilKhan-dc7mm

3 months ago
My solution: import os from pypdf import PdfWriter path = "SamplePdf/" outputDir = "OutputPdf/" if os.path.exists(path): pass else: os.mkdir(path) if os.path.exists(outputDir): pass else: os.mkdir(outputDir) print(f"Drop the input pdf files in {path} for operations.") inputFiles = os.listdir(path) inputFiles.sort() if inputFiles: print(f"The files in directory are: \n{inputFiles}") choice = str(input("Merge them? y/n\n--> ")) choice = choice.lower() if choice == "y": outputName = str(input("Enter output PDF name: ")) outputPath = os.path.join(outputDir, outputName+".pdf") merger = PdfWriter() for file in inputFiles: merger.append(f"{path}{file}") merger.write(outputPath) print("PDF successfully merged.") elif choice == "n": print("Program exited.") exit() else: print("Error: Invalid input.") exit() else: print("There are no files in directory.")
